#Text=The San Antonio Spurs ( 37 - 6 ) took care of business against the Phoenix Suns ( 13 - 31 ) on Thursday in a 117 - 89 win .
#Text=This was a mismatch of epic proportions on paper and that ended up proving to be the case on the court .
#Text=Not only have the Suns been the worst team in basketball over the last month , they have a myriad of injuries that left them with a no - name lineup on Thursday .
#Text=San Antonio did what they do best here and stifled the Suns en route to an easy win .
#Text=They held Phoenix to just 40 percent shooting and nearly doubled them in the turnover margin .
#Text=The Spurs were unconscious from long distance tonight as well , as they went 9 - for - 14 in the game from three - point range .
#Text=The San Antonio bench has been the best in the league all season and they were huge again here , as they outscored the Suns bench 66 - 24 .
#Text=The Spurs came into this game with an 11 - game winning streak and left with a simple win against a beleaguered Suns team .
#Text=They were able to rest Tony Parker and Tim Duncan here and still took care of business thanks to a great team effort .
#Text=An incredible 12 players scored at least five points tonight with Kawhi Leonard leading the bunch with 21 points of his own .
#Text=Boban Marjanovic also had his best game of his young career , as he contributed 17 points and 13 rebounds in the victory .
#Text=This marks San Antonio 's fifth wire - to - wire win of the season as well , which is a great feat on its own .
#Text=The Spurs get another easy matchup on Friday in their next game , when they take on the Los Angeles Lakers in the back end of a back - to - back set .
#Text=It 's tough for Phoenix to win any game right now , but for them to beat the Spurs with no healthy bodies is just a cruel task .
#Text=The Suns were without Eric Bledsoe , Brandon Knight , Markieff Morris , Mirza Teletovic and Jon Leuer for this game and lost P.J .
#Text=Tucker in the first quarter to an injury .
#Text=That 's just impossible to overcome , as the five starters tonight combined for 35 points per game for the season between all of them .
#Text=Devin Booker has been the one bright spot in a dark season and he had another good game here , as he tallied 24 points and five assists in the loss .
#Text=Alex Len also had a good game , as he totaled 13 points , eight rebounds and four assists in his first start in weeks .
#Text=T.J.
#Text=Warren has been the Suns best scorer at times this year and he gave the team a nice boost here with 18 points off the bench .
#Text=Tyson Chandler has been a disappointment this season , but he snatched down 20 rebounds in one of his best games of the year .
#Text=Up next for Phoenix is the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday .
